{{Infobox football biography | name= Urbano Cairo | image = Urbano Cairo.jpg | fullname = | height = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1957|05|21|df=yes}} | birth_place =[[Italy]] | death_date = | death_place = | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1= 1973 – 1975<ref name="Prosesto">{{cite web|title=Cairo, lascia il Toro e compra la Pro Sesto|url=http://www.lastampa.it/sport/cmsSezioni/quitoro/200912articoli/24434girata.asp|work=[[La Stampa]]|accessdate=2 August 2010|language=Italian|date=31 December 2009}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> | youthclubs1=[[Pro Sesto]]<ref name="Prosesto" /> | years1= | clubs1= | caps1= | goals1 = | nationalyears1= | nationalteam1= | nationalcaps1= | nationalgoals1 = }}
'''Urbano Cairo''' (born 21 May 1957) is an [[Italy|Italian]] businessman and [[chairman]] of [[Torino F.C.]].
Cairo is a native of Masio [[Alessandria]], [[Piedmont]]. His principal business interest is in [[Cairo Communication]], a business which he founded.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fabio Pavesi|title=Ecco chi è Urbano Cairo, l'uomo che vuole comprarsi il Corriere della Sera|url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2016-04-28/-ecco-chi-e-urbano-cairo-uomo-che-vuole-comprarsi-corriere-sera-193659.shtml?uuid=AC14jfHD|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|date=29 April 2016}}</ref> At as mid-2016, Cairo via [[U.T. Communications]] and UT Belgium Holding, owned 50.1% stake in Cairo Communication. U.T. Communications was also the parent company of [[Torino F.C.]]. Cairo is also the president of [[RCS MediaGroup]] 56% share.
